 <label>Table 2</label>
 <caption>
  <p>Classification Systems for Wheezing Preschool Children</p>
 </caption>
 <table frame="hsides" rules="groups">
  <thead>
   <tr>
    <th>Wheezing type (retrospective)</th>
    <th>Trigger type</th>
    <th>Asthma risk type (Asthma Predictive Index)</th>
   </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
   <tr>
    <td>
     <p>Transient early wheezers</p>
     <p>•Wheezing in the interval from 0–3 years old, not at 6 years</p>
    </td>
    <td>
     <p>Episodic, viral-triggered wheeze</p>
     <p>Multitrigger wheeze</p>
    </td>
    <td>
     <p>High risk</p>
     <p>•Has recurrent wheezing during 0–3 years old and</p>
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>
     <p>Late-onset wheezers</p>
     <p>•Wheezing at 6 years but not in the interval from 0 to 3 years old</p>
    </td>
    <td>Ref. European Respiratory Society (
     <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR60">61</xref>)
    </td>
    <td>
     <p>–Parent with asthma
      <sup>a</sup> or
     </p>
     <p>–Eczema in child
      <sup>a</sup>
     </p>
     <p>Or</p>
     <p>–2 of 3: allergic rhinitis,
      <sup>a</sup> wheezing without colds, eosinophilia
     </p>
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>
     <p>Persistent wheezers</p>
     <p>•Wheezing in the interval 0–3 years old and at 6 years old</p>
    </td>
    <td/>
    <td/>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td char="÷" align="char">Ref. Martinez et al. (
     <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR60">60</xref>)
    </td>
    <td/>
    <td>Low risk</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td/>
    <td/>
    <td>•Wheezing present but</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td/>
    <td/>
    <td>–Criteria above not met</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td/>
    <td/>
    <td>Ref. Castro-Rodriguez (
     <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR30">30</xref>)
    </td>
   </tr>
  </tbody>
 </table>
